Charles Ajunwa in Toronto, Canada Experts have implored educational institutions to embrace online learning, noting that emerging technology is having a major impact on education worldwide. According to the experts, attention has been paid to integrated learning platforms in the past decade, which they claimed the concepts are more economical and efficient than human instructors and mentors. They disclosed this yesterday during the official opening of this year’s Online Learning themed ‘Performance and Learning in the Digital Age’ organised by the Media Edge Communications at the Westin Harbour Castle, Toronto, Canada.